extolled the virtues of governors who became president 
or three of them anyway 
some of our finest presidents some of our strongest 
international leaders were governors franklin roosevelt woodrow 
wilson theodore roosevelt dukakis said in the first 
presidential debate 
he did not mention the last two presidents both of them former 
governers whose foreign policy performances have brought mixed 
reviews 
ronald reagan a twoterm california governor is regularly 
lambasted by critics who say he is unfamiliar with the nitty gritty 
of national security he is faulted for such acts as the 1983 
invasion of grenada and the 1986 bombing of libya and for moving 
slowly on arms control his record as president will be tainted by 
the irancontra affair as well 
jimmy carter who was governor of georgia is blamed by 
conservatives for reacting poorly to revolutions in iran and 
nicaragua and for allowing us influence abroad to deteriorate 
if elected dukakis would be the third man in a row to move from 
the state house to the white house without having held a senior 
federal job 
only one other former governor wilson of new jersey has become 
president in this century without previously holding top elected or 
appointed federal office 
franklin roosevelt lauded by dukakis was assistant secretary 
of the navy during world war i before he served as governor of new 
york theodore roosevelt held identical posts at the turn of the 
century before becoming vice president and then president 
dukakis doesnt have those entries on his resume but like 
others before him he is trying to create a lot of ersatz 
credentials in foreign policy said stephen hess who was an aide 
to former president nixon 
they go on trade missions they join the council on foreign 
relations or the trilateral commission which is what carter did 
said hess now a scholar at the liberal brookings institution in 
washington 
or they ride tanks and meet with foreign leaders 
governors who are elected president rely on a brain trust but 
so does everybody else too as the field becomes more 
specialized said hess even richard nixon who was truly 
engaged in foreign policy and made it his life interest brought in 
