orchard woman was treated for the illness after eating contaminated 
oysters from the area a week ago 
shellfish poisoning is caused by an invisible odorless and 
tasteless organism that grows naturally in shellfish tissue and 
multiplies rapidly in warmer water it does not threaten dother sea 
life but it can sicken and even kill people who eat elevated 
levels of the toxin 
it is called red tide because of the reddish discoloration of 
sea water caused by the organism 
state and federal agencies said the ban on shellfishing applies 
to sport and commercial fishermen and includes all clams oysters 
mussels and scallops 
state officials said in a news release that all commercial 
shellfish taken from the affected area since oct 1 were being 
removed from wholesale and retail sale and will be tested for the 
toxin 
south puget sound commercial shellfish go to wholesalers and 
retailers in washington california oregon alaska hawaii 
pennsylvania maine and new york 
south puget sound produces twothirds of the puget sound 
harvest and washington state is the nations largest oyster 
producer 
symptoms of shellfish poisoning include vomiting nausea muscle 
weakness and tingling of lips mouth and teeth the news release 
said loss of balance and lack of muscular coordination can follow 
those struck generally do not die but elderly people and those 
with other medical conditions can be affected more severely 
