houses komarov wrote in a power plant newspaper quoted by pravda 
but by the time normal life can return all the houses will be 
equally dilapidated and living in them will be impossible he was 
quoted as saying there will be scarcely anything to preserve at 
all 
pravda noted that the town of gden is about the same distance 
from the power plant as chernobyl and has been decontaminated and 
repopulated 
