democracies that make up nearly all of noncommunist europe it 
aims to coordinate european legislation through a series of accords 
and to encourage unity democracy and human rights 
the court of human rights has unusual power for an international 
judicial body with the right to assign damages to the losing party 
in a case or to expel a country from the council of europe 
