the jewish founders of brandeis wanted to create a nonsectarian 
school in the tradition of such universities as harvard and notre 
dame whose origins were religious but whose mission was quality 
education 
it was established at a time when some universities limited 
enrollment of jews and other minorities 
in 1948 a lot of top universities still had quota systems for 
jews and catholics and blacks were hardly an issue then said 
david merkowitz spokesman for the washingtonbased american 
