like that is important in educational diversity 
today the student body is estimated to be about 65 percent 
jewish thirteen percent are black hispanic and asian 
a place of excellence thats why brandeis was founded there 
were quotas against jews but there was a need beyond that said 
brandeis president evelyn handler 
brandeis was a maverick from the start only two of its seven 
founding trustees had been to college the school lacked a single 
large endowment but instead built itself on many small donations 
the university is among the most expensive private colleges at 
20000 for tuition room and board 
the school was named for the late us supreme court justice 
louis d brandeis a liberal jurist and the first jew on the high 
court when he was appointed in 1916 he died in 1941 
the small liberal arts university on the grounds of a defunct 
