<TEXT>
the space shuttle discovery arrived 
home atop a jumbo jet saturday five days after completing 
americas first manned space mission since the challenger tragedy 
a boeing 747 with the shuttle bolted on its back descended 
through a cloud deck and glided to a runway touchdown at 704 pm 
edt as darkness descended on the kennedy space center the return 
flight began saturday morning at edwards air force base calif 
because the kennedy runway is not heavily lighted and because of 
cloudy weather nasa officials were considering diverting the 
shuttle aircraft to eglin air force base in northwest florida for 
an overnight stay 
but half an hour before landing an advance plane reported 
conditions favorable and the jumbo jet came on in 
thousands of spectators turned out to applaud the return lining 
roads and river banks and creating huge traffic jams at the space 
center most of them were among the hundreds of thousands who were 
here to cheer discoverys departure on sept 29 
technicians planned to remove the shuttle from its carrier plane 
overnight and tomorrow and then tow it to a processing facility to 
prepare it for its next flight officials reported it returned from 
space in such good shape that little refurbishment work will be 
needed 
the shuttlejet combination made the threehour run after a 
refueling stop at kelly air force base in san antonio tex 
nasas modified boeing 747 took off from edwards air force base 
in californias mojave desert military base at 1054 am edt with 
the shuttle bolted to its back said nancy lovato spokeswoman for 
the national aeronautics and space administration 
it was a fitting finish to a super mission ms lovato said 
it was the prettiest takeoff from edwards that ive ever seen 
and ive seen them all it was as graceful as the landing 
the flight from edwards to san antonio was uneventful said joe 
algranti pilot of 747 
we had real good weather all the way with a little bit of 
tail wind he said we are glad to be back in business 
discovery and its fiveman crew landed on the hard clay rogers 
dry lake bed at edwards last monday four days after its launch 
from cape canaveral fla more than 400000 people came to cheer 
the returning astronauts 
it was the first shuttle flight since challenger blew up during 
liftoff on jan 28 1986 killing all seven crew members 
the highlight of discoverys flight was the successful 
deployment of a 100 million tracking and data relay communications 
satellite a twin of a satellite destroyed aboard challenger 
the next shuttle mission will be flown by atlantis which will 
carry a classified defense department payload when it is launched 
in late november 
discoverys next flight scheduled for feb 18 will deploy 
another tdrs satellite for nasa communications 
when discovery landed in california reporters asked richard 
truly nasas associate administrator for space flight if the 
shuttle and its jet carrier could take a more circuitous route to 
florida so it could be seen by more americans 
i wish we could fly it around but thats not its purpose 
truly replied its purpose is to get back to the cape and to get 
back into space where it belongs 
discovery was prepared for its return to florida by nasa 
technicians who photographed and replaced damaged heatshield 
tiles purged fuel from its main engines and orbital maneuvering 
engines installed a tailcone and locks to prevent control surfaces 
from fluttering during the flight then hoisted it atop the 747 
nasa bought the 225footlong jumbo jet from american airlines 
for 15 million in 1974 and at first used it for flight research 
projects boeing modified the jet for nasa in 1976 so it could 
carry the shuttles 
the 747 was reinforced and its engines were upgraded to increase 
takeoff thrust 
nasa recently purchased a second 747 to ferry shuttles 
crosscountry once it is modified the second jet will be based in 
el paso texas 
